question_results.question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? A design by Max is either evocative or dreamy.
question_results.combined_program:
set(auto).
assign(max_seconds, 5).
assign(max_mem, 1024).
# Predicates:
DesignStyle(x) ::: x is a design style of Zaha Hadid.
Timeless(x) ::: x is timeless.
MassProductDesign(x) ::: x is a mass product design.
DesignStyleOfKellyWearstler(x) ::: x is a design style of Kelly Wearstler.
Evocative(x) ::: x is evocative.
Dreamy(x) ::: x is dreamy.
DesignByMax(x) ::: x is a design by Max.

# Premises:
∀x (DesignStyle(x) → Timeless(x))
∀x (MassProductDesign(x) → ¬Timeless(x))
∀x (DesignStyle(x) → ¬DesignStyleOfKellyWearstler(x))
∀x (DesignStyleOfKellyWearstler(x) → Evocative(x))
∀x (DesignStyleOfKellyWearstler(x) → Dreamy(x))
∀x (DesignByMax(x) → (Timeless(x) → (MassProductDesign(x) ∧ Evocative(x))))
∃x DesignStyle(x) ∨ ∃x DesignStyleOfKellyWearstler(x)

# Conclusion:
∀x (DesignByMax(x) → (Evocative(x) ∨ Dreamy(x)))
